    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This behaviour is expected. If you are sending multiple private transactions for the same account (\"from\") to the same privacy group with the same nonce, only the first transaction will succeed, the other transactions will fail because the nonce is too low. \r\nEthSigner is using priv_getTransactionCount to set the nonce (if it is not provided in the private transaction). priv_getTransactionCount will result in the same nonce until the private state of the privacy group is updated.    \r\nIf it is required that multiple private transactions are sent to the same privacy group using the same account within a short timeframe the nonce management cannot be done by EthSigner. \r\nEthSigner does have a  retry mechanism for nonce too low errors, but that does not work for private transactions.\r\nThis issue should be closed.\r\nWe should open an issue against EthSigner to support nonce too low retries for private transactions as well.",
